        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 8:12PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 810 PM MDT, numerous weather spotters reported a thunderstorm
producing pea size hail near Black Forest, or 10 miles northeast of
Colorado Springs, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Trained weather spotters.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Black Forest, Falcon, Cimarron Hills, Peterson Space Force Base, Air
Force Academy, and Colorado Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
